    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-09T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-09T10:00:00-05:00" n="293"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d293">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.48/1528: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Algiers</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-09T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 9, 1943—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:29 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>834. From Murphy from Bernstein<note n="62" xml:id="d293fn62">Presumably Edward
                        M. Bernstein, Assistant Director of the Division of Monetary Research,
                        Treasury Department.</note> for Morgenthau.<note n="63" xml:id="d293fn63"
                        >Henry Morgenthau, Jr., Secretary of the Treasury.</note> Reference Madrid’s
                    1099, April 30 to Department.<note n="61" xml:id="d293fn61">Not printed.</note>
                    French request transfer additional $300,000 to Malaise at Madrid for expenses
                    maintenance and evacuation to North Africa of French refugees in Spain. Approval
                    of transfer is recommended as it is continuation of program for which transfer
                    of funds was previously approved.</p>
                <pb facs="0310" n="300" xml:id="pg_300"/>
                <p>French also request transfer of $200,000 to Madrid for support of French schools
                    in Spain which have rallied to Giraud and are opposing Vichy control. We have no
                    additional information concerning the merits of this latter request.</p>
                <p>To Department. Repeated to Madrid. [Bernstein. Murphy.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wiley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
